<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is usually easily recognised by its large carolla and the palmately-lobed discolorous leaves. However, as with many species in the 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Pharbitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pharbitis</taxonomicName>
Clade, the leaves may be entire or lobed. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gentry</emphasis>
1788 and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ruiz et al.</emphasis>
2009-278 differ from other specimens in having entire, strongly abaxially sericeous leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Placement of this species in the 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Pharbitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pharbitis</taxonomicName>
Clade is provisional.
</paragraph>
